<br>
I still had my guns drawn and I was not about to let anything happen to myself. And I was going to get that bomb away from Taylee so she couldn't be stupid enough to follow George's selfish orders. Frankly right now I had lost all interest in Taylees blood and as it was my nature to stick it to the vampires every chance I got, well I just wanted to spit in Cale's face by running off with his brother's ghoul. I was still curious also if George was pulling a bluff about the bomb.<br>
<br>
So I moved, fast enough that George could not have seen, only the vampires including Cale could possibly have. My path was true as I swept past Taylee, the tip of my blade clipping the package and sending it sliding far away from her and landing at Cale's feet instead. Just as quickly I then leaped up onto a light post were I crouched with my guns trained on them all for I was now out of the circle.<br>
