Cale watched as the two females battled it out. He had to admit, they both displayed impressive skills. He could have had Rayne killed in a second, but this was fun. As for Taylea, a wave of his hand and her escape route was blocked off.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile, George was watching the ladies play hotpotato with his cig pack. Then when Rayne put bullets through it, he mouthed &quot;Shit&quot;. <br>
<br>
Cale watched the pack turned to shreds, and then nothing. &quot;You were bluffing!?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Looks that way doesn't it. Question is, where's the real bomb?&quot; With that he through the detonator at Cale who caught it of course. What he wasn't expecting however was the small puff of smoke fused with essence of garlic that came out and caught his eyes.<br>
<br>
On George's end, immediately after the detonator left his hands, he reached into his coat and grabbed a couple of rare items. Tear gas made of the same thing as in the detonator. About the time Cale was being blinded, the pins were out of the canisters and the bombs were on the ground, spewing smoke and gas into the air. His lungs full before he became invisible to the vamps' eyes. Hidden from all eyes, even Rayne's, he flipped open the manhole cover at his feet and grabbed Taylee and the baby. Holding them close, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Too close for a ghoul</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, George jumped into the hole and replaced the cover. Upon landing his brace shook and his leg hurt even more, but he fought above it. &quot;Let's go.&quot; He said, pulling Taylee along and not giving her a choice.<br>
<br>
(George and Taylea continued in Warehouse district. And Rayne, if you insist on following, give us a few minutes to get some arguments in the mix.)<br>
<br>
Cale waited for the smoke to disappear. He blinked and physically shook with anger. &quot;I WANT THEM FOUND. NOW!!&quot; He doubted even Rayne could deny the strength that radiated from him at that moment. And what's worse is he hadn't calmed down at all.<br>
