ason I never carried it. Guess it was about time I did.<br>
<br>
Knowing that the manhole, plus the sound of it clanking only seconds before had to be George's escape route, I knew I had to follow him. Now it mattered not to me what he did with his life but he had fucked up my evening so far and I wanted to make sure his did not go so well anymore either. Take something from me and I'd take something from you was how I thought. Humans were so stupid and pathetic, I praised the fact I was not one of them.<br>
<br>
Quickly I leaped off the lamp post and into the darkness, not caring what Cale or the other vampires did. If they followed me the I would have to change my plans but for now I had some very good ideas. It was not possible for two humans and a baby to get very far fast in the tunnels and with my sense of smell, I would be able to track them down easily. I signaled my companion in the truck to continue on, there was no way he would be able to follow me. Playing a little deception of my own, I made it look like I got in the vehicle with him as he drove off but in reality I used the truck to block the view of me climbing into another manehole and closing the lid.<br>
<br>
Darkness and stench surrounded me as I walked back through the tunnels. In the darkness, my dhampire vision played out well and I was able to see foot prints of the two in the sludge. Following them was easy enough though they did vanish when the floor got hard, but the trail was simple enough to pick up again and I knew I had to be headed towards the warehouse district. Now that was a place I hardly went myself alone for it was the vampire front for importing food in human form. The place always swarmed with vampires, even in the so called day and though they left you alone for the most part, should something go wrong then welcome to your fate. But nothing would go wrong tonight for what vampire there would care I was after humans?<br>
<br>
The stench of the sewer tunnels grew as I progressed and I stopped for a moment to look around. It was then I heard the sound of clicking claws upon steel and I knew what approached. There was no place for me to hide as the shadowy forms approached so I stood my ground with weapons drawn, my eyes going from one to the next. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Just fucking great... Were creatures... Shit. This is definatly not good</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
