<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Iris... I am a voice from your past and requesting your company...&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> he send an unreadable thought into her head that only she could read. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Continue your life with these ones if you wish but all I ask is for a moment of your time... We have much to catch up on for it has been a while since I have seen you. Curious yet as to who I am? The come to me... follow my thoughts. I am just a block away to your right.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Decide later if you wish to carry on with those of our kind that would harm you, but I offer you a chance at doing better then that.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> he finished his guarded thought to her and waited for her response. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwynnethdelioncourt>Gwynneth de Lioncourt</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://animatedgif.net/bulletsballs/flasharrowrt_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#8B4513>(9/16/03 9:01 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.jasminebecketgriffith.com/boredfairy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Without Hope</span><hr size=1> Iris didn't show any physical sign that she'd heard it, but she had. A voice had spoken to her mind, and it seemed vaguely familiar. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Give me a minute to get the hell out of this redhead/ghoul hunt and I'll be there...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> she sent the thought back, careful to cloak her mind to keep Cale from seeing into it. <br>
<br>
&quot;I'd love to run along and help you, Cale darling, but... I have some other business to attend to.&quot; With that, she dashed off, leaving a purple-black blur in her wake.<br>
<br>
After a few moments, she arrived near where the voice had called to her, but she didn't see anyone around. She glanced into the shadows, thinking that she saw a humanoid shape in one of them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhekath>Rhekath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#8B4513>(9/16/03 9:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Without Hope</span><hr size=1> &quot;Time hasn't changed you one bit... still curious as ever my dear.&quot; the darkness spoke before David made himself known by stepping out into the dim light. A smile played across his lips as he looked her over, pleased  to see she was still as beautiful as ever.<br>
<br>
&quot;It has been a while since we have seen eachother, but surely I don't need to introduce myself do I?&quot; he flashed her a charming smile before glancing down the street. &quot;But before we talk, lets get off the street because with the commotion going on down there with the others will draw attention I am not in the mood for.&quot; <br>
<br>
Quickly stepping over to a doorway behind him, David pushed it open and invited her inside before closing the door behind her. The room was lit with a single lanturn from the ceiling and Dave walked into the middle of the room before stopping and looking at her once more. &quot;Its good to see time hasn't changed you... now are you curious as to why I called for you?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwynnethdelioncourt>Gwynneth de Lioncourt</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://animatedgif.net/bulletsballs/flasharrowrt_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#8B4513>(9/17/03 5:06 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.jasminebecketgriffith.com/boredfairy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Without Hope</span><hr size=1> Iris crossed her arms and tried not to smile. It had been a long time, but for David to suddenly appear like this... Something itched at the back of her mind, telling her not to drop her guard as of yet.<br>
<br>
She nodded slightly. &quot;To say I'm curious would be a bit of an understatement, so.. What's up?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhekath>Rhekath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#8B4513>(9/17/03 9:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Without Hope</span><hr size=1> Dave settled back against the wall, his eyes getting a good look at her tall slender figure, a pleased look teased slightly in his gaze.<br>
<br>
&quot;Since I met you Iris, I have gone deep into the underworld of our vampire nation. I have seen things that could cause even the ancients to shudder and learned things I was happier not knowing.&quot; Dave began slowly, speaking his thoughts carefully.<br>
<br>
&quot;I belong to a sociaty that's soul purpose is to hunt and kill the hunters of our kind. I must say you put yourself in a fair bit of danger just by being in the presense of two of them.&quot; he spoke of the interesting dance he had witnessed between them all earlier. &quot;The human is of little concern to us of the order, we have plans for him but the red head has been causing us a fair amount of trouble.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Midnight is new to New York but already she has slain many of our kind... I warn you to be careful because no only do I see you run into her and start a fight with her, I see you with a vampire that could care less about your life. Now I could be wrong it what I saw...&quot; he paused, his eyes looking towards the floor as he stroked his goatee softly.<br>
<br>
&quot;I really was not looking for you till I sensed you and now that I have found you I would like to offer you a place with me. We vampires are faced with a war... Humans blame us for their extinction yet they are to blame for the pollution that has made this city our home. They gather in secret and with the Were creatures... I need vampires like you... And if I remember correctly you love excitement...&quot; he charmed her with a grin as he looked back up into her eyes to wait for her response. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhekath>Rhekath</A> at: 9/17/03 9:25 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwynnethdelioncourt>Gwynneth de Lioncourt</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://animatedgif.net/bulletsballs/flasharrowrt_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#8B4513>(9/18/03 5:38 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.jasminebecketgriffith.com/boredfairy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Without Hope</span><hr size=1> &quot;Dave, honey... A place with you could be more dangerous than deciding to sleep on a park bench when you know there's a serial killer on the loose that's just escaped from the state pen.&quot; Iris replied with a little laugh, still finding it slightly unsettling that she had to look up to meet his gaze. She was so used to having to slump and glance down to look people in the eyes...<br>
<br>
She folded her arms casually across her waist and leaned back against the wall opposite the other vampire, sighing softly. She looked away from him and said softly, more to herself than to him, &quot;The weres aren't much of a threat. They're a lot of talk, but so long as you can be faster, they can never best you in any sort of fight. Unless there're more than five of them. Then you're fucked,&quot; she added, looking back up and across at him. <br>
<br>
She was silent a moment, her eyes steadily meeting his gaze without blinking. She finally closed her eyes, slowly, her coal dark lashes coming to rest on her snowy cheeks. &quot;I... will stay with you, David.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhekath>Rhekath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#8B4513>(9/18/03 5:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Without Hope</span><hr size=1> Dave listened to her weigh the odds and seem to find absolutely no reason to come with him but when she said she would, he arched his right brow in question. &quot;I take it you want the danger if not being with me is safer...&quot; his lips turned into a small grin as he lifted himself away from the wall and stepped near her.<br>
<br>
He hid his delight in her agreement to go with him because it was just not the tough guy way so instead he stood there with arms crossed over his chest, his eyes looking down to hers slightly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Since you are coming with me, there is no reason to hang around here. My car is around the corner, lets go shall we?&quot; Dave invited her to leave with him right now. &quot;Its good seeing you again, and having you around... ready?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwynnethdelioncourt>Gwynneth de Lioncourt</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://animatedgif.net/bulletsballs/flasharrowrt_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#8B4513>(9/18/03 6:20 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.jasminebecketgriffith.com/boredfairy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Without Hope</span><hr size=1> Iris's breath hitched in her throat and her deadened heart fluttered against her ribcage like a trapped bird at how close David was to her. She didn't physically show it, but she was sure he could hear her heart beating faster with his preternatural hearing. <br>
<br>
She nodded slightly with a little smile. &quot;Good to see you, too. Let's go.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhekath>Rhekath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#8B4513>(9/18/03 7:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Without Hope</span><hr size=1> The quickening of her heart beat sounded in his ears as he stepped even closer to her just to excite her more. His lips drew close to hers as his breath bathed her face from their closeness when he leaned down. &quot;Well then Iris, lets go.&quot;<br>
<br>
Like the tease that he was, Dave brushed past her and towards the door without even a look back until he had checked to see that the coast was clear. One could never be to safe and Dave knew the other vampire had to still be out there. But that was not his concern once he saw the coast was clear and with that he took Iris's hand and lead her outside.<br>
<br>
Quickly he lead her around the back of the building to were a black 1997 Corvette sat in the darkness sat. The lights flashed as he disarmed the alarm and opened the passanger door to let her in. It clicked when he closed it and moved around to his side of the car and climbed in. &quot;Its almost morning, do you want to come back to my place or go to yours?&quot; he asked as he turned the key in the ignition to bring the powerful engine to life. The tires squealled as he shifted into gear and took off down the street, knowing he could change direction if she wanted to go somewhere other then where he was headed which was for the moment back to his house. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwynnethdelioncourt>Gwynneth de Lioncourt</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://animatedgif.net/bulletsballs/flasharrowrt_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#8B4513>(9/18/03 7:30 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.jasminebecketgriffith.com/boredfairy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Without Hope</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Damnable tease...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Iris thought to herself, cloaking the thought although he'd probably get the gist of it, regardless.<br>
<br>
His question gave her pause, and temporarily saddened the tall vampiress. She had no place to call her own, really. &quot;Your place is fine...&quot; she said simply, although they were already off and down the road. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhekath>Rhekath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#8B4513>(9/18/03 8:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Without Hope</span><hr size=1> Dave could tell that time had not changed the enjoyment they both recieved from eachother's company. Though nothing had ever happened between them in their past, Dave could sense that maybe this time would be a little different. Maybe this time they would take their feelings into action.<br>
<br>
&quot;My place is fine, I have a spare bed you can sleep on if you like.&quot; he replied as they drove down the deserted streets towards his home. As they drove since he lived on the other side of the city, he decided to ask her a bit of her life recently and see if she was attached to anyone. &quot;So Iris... how has life been? Still single or bound?&quot; he charmed her with a smile that would have told her he did not care if she was because that might not stop him. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwynnethdelioncourt>Gwynneth de Lioncourt</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://animatedgif.net/bulletsballs/flasharrowrt_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#8B4513>(9/18/03 8:58 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.jasminebecketgriffith.com/boredfairy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Without Hope</span><hr size=1> Iris just shook her head with a little laugh. &quot;I'm single, Dave. You know me. I can't be held down, and there aren't many guys strong enough or stony enough to even try to hold me down...&quot; she grinned a little at that. <br>
<br>
&quot;Life has been... odd. My folks passed away a while back, but so far as I know, my sister's still alive somewhere. I've been afraid to look for her, because I don't want to see her already growing old when I haven't aged at all. It just.. goes against nature, and I know I wouldn't be able to handle it.&quot; Iris went silent a moment.<br>
<br>
Her dark eyes glanced over at David in the intimate darkness of the car, her voice almost sad as she asked, &quot;Do I have to sleep on the guest bed, or is yours big enough to share?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhekath>Rhekath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#8B4513>(9/19/03 7:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Without Hope</span><hr size=1> Dave sat there in the darkness listening to her as she talked though his eyes watched the road lit up by his car lights. The darkness hid his slight smile as she mentioned the sleeping arrangements but he could not disagree with her. Time was just a good of time as any to get done what they never had before when they had met long ago.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well my bed is big enough if you wish to sleep there instead... I warn you I'll be sleeping there to.&quot; Dave cautioned her though he knew full well that was probably her reason for wanting to sleep there in the first place. &quot;Sharing isn't something I have done in a while but its you so I'll get used to it.&quot;<br>
<br>
The idea of the tall slender raven haired girl lying so close to him he could feel the heat of her skin drove his senses a little wild. Home seemed so far away now but with the speed they drove they would get there soon enough. He shifted through the gears as they rounded a corner and increased speed once more towards 100miles an hour, his home now only a few blocks away.<br>
<br>
&quot;Your sister... do you even know if she is alive with all this destruction around us? Humans are disappearing very quickly... sad really...&quot; he made idle conversation as they drove the last few blocks and pulled up to his house. His house was located on a deserted block, everything very run down but his car did not stick out as he hid it in the garage. <br>
<br>
Dave lead her inside his home which was rather well furnished and even had running water. His bedroom was to the back of the house, the windows all up with iron plating like every other house in the area since this was a vampire sector. &quot;Welcome to my home, make yourself comfortable.&quot;<br>
